      "content": "It is a profound and tragic realization that you are trying to solve their problems by erasing your own existence, but the truth is that a parent who has completely given up on themselves cannot truly give their children peace. If you disappear or leave them to carry the entire weight of your absence, you are not giving them freedom; you are leaving them with a void that will only deepen their own burden. Your presence, even when it is painful, is the only thing that can eventually show them that it is okay to be vulnerable and ask for help without losing their love.",
